<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Build a Meshery MCP Tool on TCS Labs Academy</title><link>https://meshery-extensions.github.io/tcslabs-academy/pr-preview/pr-36/challenges/deea6061-b6be-49a9-ad1c-f1a5c32e1fa9/build-a-meshery-mcp-tool/</link><description>Recent content in Build a Meshery MCP Tool on TCS Labs Academy</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://meshery-extensions.github.io/tcslabs-academy/pr-preview/pr-36/challenges/deea6061-b6be-49a9-ad1c-f1a5c32e1fa9/build-a-meshery-mcp-tool/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Build a Meshery MCP Tool</title><link>https://meshery-extensions.github.io/tcslabs-academy/pr-preview/pr-36/challenges/deea6061-b6be-49a9-ad1c-f1a5c32e1fa9/build-a-meshery-mcp-tool/lab/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://meshery-extensions.github.io/tcslabs-academy/pr-preview/pr-36/challenges/deea6061-b6be-49a9-ad1c-f1a5c32e1fa9/build-a-meshery-mcp-tool/lab/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction" class="heading-link"&gt;
 Introduction
 &lt;a href="#introduction" class="heading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink to this heading"&gt;🔗&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this challenge you will build a small &lt;a href="https://modelcontextprotocol.io/"&gt;Model Context Protocol&lt;/a&gt;
(MCP) tool that gives a coding agent a safe, structured view of your &lt;a href="https://meshery.io/"&gt;Meshery&lt;/a&gt;
and cluster state. You will start &lt;strong&gt;read-only&lt;/strong&gt; - the safe foundation for any agent integration -
and prove the agent can answer real questions about your infrastructure through your tool.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id="prerequisites" class="heading-link"&gt;
 Prerequisites
 &lt;a href="#prerequisites" class="heading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink to this heading"&gt;🔗&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Kubernetes cluster with &lt;a href="https://docs.meshery.io/"&gt;Meshery&lt;/a&gt; running and connected.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A coding agent that supports MCP servers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A language you are comfortable in (any language with an MCP server library works).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2 id="step-1---define-one-read-only-tool" class="heading-link"&gt;
 Step 1 - Define one read-only tool
 &lt;a href="#step-1---define-one-read-only-tool" class="heading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink to this heading"&gt;🔗&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Design a single, well-scoped tool. Good first choice: &lt;code&gt;get_workload_status&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Build a Meshery MCP Tool - Exam</title><link>https://meshery-extensions.github.io/tcslabs-academy/pr-preview/pr-36/challenges/deea6061-b6be-49a9-ad1c-f1a5c32e1fa9/build-a-meshery-mcp-tool/exam/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://meshery-extensions.github.io/tcslabs-academy/pr-preview/pr-36/challenges/deea6061-b6be-49a9-ad1c-f1a5c32e1fa9/build-a-meshery-mcp-tool/exam/</guid><description/></item></channel></rss>